 the expression predicted in\nthe literature. In either of those cases, we have $\\lambda\\sim \\Big(\\frac{\\log\n\\log N}{\\log N}\\Big)^{\\alpha}$, for different values of $\\alpha>0$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Jun 2021 17:45:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 13 Aug 2021 19:53:42 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 19 Sep 2021 14:28:49 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 29 Mar 2022 15:37:51 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 15 Feb 2023 23:42:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-17"}
