_{B}\\gtrsim-1$. A spectrum with two breaks could be typical of GRB\nprompt emission, though hard to identify with current detectors. Instrumental\ndesign such that conceived for the THESEUS space mission, extending from 0.3\nkeV to several MeV and featuring a larger effective area with respect to\nFermi/GBM, can reveal a larger fraction of GRBs with a spectral energy break.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Jun 2021 18:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-25"}
